section: This Services Agreement (this "Agreement") is entered into on October 1, 2019 and is made effective as of November 1, 2019 (the "Effective Date")
explanation: There is a contradiction, the agreement is entered on one date but is not effective until a later date, this causes confustion.

section: Provider may not make any change in the Provider Representatives without the prior consent of the Recipient. Provider Representatives shall be dedicated to solely providing the Services to Recipient and shall not provide any such services or resources to Provider or any other customer of Provider.
explanation: The Provider Representatives are not able to work for any other company other than the recipient but can use subcontractors to preform services. It is unclear if these subcontractors can provide services to another company.

section: 3.1 Termination of Agreement. This Agreement be deemed effective as of the Effective Date, Agreement and shall terminate on December 31, 2020, unless terminated earlier in accordance with Section 3.2.
explanation: The language is confusing because it has the phrase 'Agreement be deemed effective as of the Effective Date, Agreement' this is a structural flaw in the agreement.
